  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs tunable configuration parameters including base mesh size (nominal 0.15 mm near-wall refinement), hemolysis power-law threshold stress (τ_th = 50 Pa), and iterative convergence tolerance (residual target 1e-5). Validation results are reported at these chosen settings; however, no structured configuration node is linked to this assurance package and the Context of Use does not constrain which parameter values must be used at deployment.",
